{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17588531","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17588531"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T09:09:57+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T09:09:57+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15167"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15167","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15167"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.06,0.09,0,0.86,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7858"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62754"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7858","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7858"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15167"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48202"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"2058"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4936"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7882"},{"type":"tags","id":"8095"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"},{"type":"tags","id":"11163"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19156"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19159"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20440"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62754","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/62754"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA dental student is learning about mucosal lesions that can be found in the oral cavity. The one in particular that they are asked to identify is shown in the photograph (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is most commonly associated with the changes shown?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Oral lichen planus","Hairy leukoplakia","Chemical burn","Oral candidiasis","Frictional keratosis"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe photograph shows numerous discrete white patches on the dorsum of the tongue. This is the characteristic appearance of \u003Cstrong\u003Eoral candidiasis\u003C/strong\u003E. Oral candidiasis (thrush) is the most common cause of white patches in the oral cavity. It is caused by overgrowth of \u003Cem\u003ECandida albicans\u003C/em\u003E and presents as creamy white, removable plaques. This fungal infection is most often seen in immunocompromised patients, those with diabetes and those with poor dental hygiene.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHairy leukoplakia\u003C/strong\u003E presents as white, confluent, corrugated patches typically on the lateral borders of the tongue and is associated with Epstein-Barr virus infection in immunocompromised patients. (Image)\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOral lichen planus\u003C/strong\u003E appears as white, lacy streaks on the oral mucosa (Wickham\u0027s striae) and is an autoimmune condition.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChemical burns\u003C/strong\u003E from substances like aspirin can cause white patches where the caustic agent contacts the mucosa.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFrictional keratosis\u003C/strong\u003E appears as white patches in areas of chronic irritation, commonly along the bite line of the cheek.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["White patches in the oral cavity can be caused by various conditions including candidiasis, leukoplakia, lichen planus, and chemical burns","Oral hairy leukoplakia is specifically associated with Epstein-Barr virus infection in immunocompromised patients"],"references":["Mohammed F, Fairozekhan AT. Oral Leukoplakia. [Updated 2023 Jul 17]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK442013/","Dilhari A, Weerasekera MM, Siriwardhana A, Maheshika O, Gunasekara C, Karunathilaka S, Nagahawatte A, Fernando N. Candida infection in oral leukoplakia: an unperceived public health problem. Acta Odontol Scand. 2016 Oct;74(7):565-569. doi: 10.1080/00016357.2016.1220018. Epub 2016 Aug 19. PMID: 27538681.","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48202"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15167"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21192"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21193"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21192","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21192"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/WRq3b1An6RqPMZXz1RgrqjBJT2etiv.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/WRq3b1An6RqPMZXz1RgrqjBJT2etiv.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":640,"height":454}},{"type":"media","id":"21193","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21193"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/pz4zCTp173B1ofD6UuBx0HfJC3ODxW.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/pz4zCTp173B1ofD6UuBx0HfJC3ODxW.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":314,"height":480}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48202","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/48202"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-18T17:38:55+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-18T17:39:27+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7858"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62754"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":